We claim the money that we need, Father, in Jesus'name, to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we dare ask or think.

00:59:27.747 --> 00:59:38.744
Father, how you provide for us and take care of us and our households, that every person that's represented here will lack no good thing physically, mentally, emotionally, financially.

00:59:38.745 --> 00:59:43.843
We're calling it in right now in Jesus'name. We're calling in the blessing.

00:59:43.844 --> 00:59:47.884
You can hold my hand. Father, we call it in right now in Jesus'name.

00:59:47.885 --> 00:59:53.596
We're speaking to the finances to come forth. We bind the devil off of our finances.

00:59:53.597 --> 01:00:00.612
We break the power of debt. We break the power of poverty and lack and not enough and barely getting by.

01:00:00.613 --> 01:00:05.914
We release the blessing and increase and multiplication and favor in the name of Jesus.

01:00:05.915 --> 01:00:24.239
Father, I thank you, Lord, that every one of them is delivered from drug addictions, from all kinds of bondage, from all addictions, from pornography and lustful thoughts and PTSD and all kinds of things that are involved in the mind.

01:00:24.240 --> 01:00:29.830
Father, I call them healed and whole and well and delivered in Jesus'name.

01:00:29.831 --> 01:00:34.255
We thank you, Lord, for whom the Son has set free is free indeed.

01:00:34.256 --> 01:00:37.756
And Father, we thank you, Lord, that they're not bound by pornography anymore.

01:00:37.757 --> 01:00:52.759
The people that are struggling over this, and they keep saying, "Brandon, there's so many people saying, 'I got lust issues, I got all this going on with me.'"I thank you, Father, that they're free from that in Jesus'name.

01:00:52.760 --> 01:01:01.606
We call their brain free from that. We call their brain healed and whole and well from—is it opioids? Opioid addiction?

01:01:01.607 --> 01:01:08.872
No, I'm talking about like it's oxytocin—it's whatever it is when they're looking at that trash—and dopamine. Thank you, baby.

01:01:08.873 --> 01:01:15.439
Father, I thank you, Lord, that their dopamine levels would be normal, that their body wouldn't be so addicted to this stuff.

01:01:15.440 --> 01:01:23.744
Father, I thank you, Lord, for their freedom in Jesus'name.

01:01:23.745 --> 01:01:29.364
It dies tonight. We're not moved by what we see. We're not moved by what we feel.

01:01:29.365 --> 01:01:34.399
We're moved by what the word of God says. And we thank you, Lord, that they're free in Jesus'name.

01:01:34.400 --> 01:01:45.822
And we call them free even from the drugs: fentanyl, OxyContin, and Lortabs, and all those things like that. Adderall.

01:01:45.823 --> 01:01:59.838
Father, I thank you, Lord, for freedom from Adderall, freedom from OxyContin, freedom from Lortab, that the blessing of the Lord is on their lives in Jesus'name.

01:01:59.839 --> 01:02:05.702
And healing and deliverance is on them, Father. And we thank you, Lord, for that in Jesus'name.

01:02:05.703 --> 01:02:14.879
We thank you, Lord, that their marriage is restored. We call forth marriages to be restored right now in Jesus'name.

01:02:14.880 --> 01:02:20.537
People feeling inadequate finally. Thank you, Holy Ghost.

01:02:20.538 --> 01:02:30.234
People feeling inadequate. "I'm not good enough."That's what I hear.

01:02:30.235 --> 01:02:44.975
"I'm not good enough."Feeling inadequacy with their spiritual walk with the Father.

01:02:44.976 --> 01:02:51.136
The Lord said you—He just said, "Diana, pray over it."People feeling inadequate, that they don't have what it takes.

01:02:51.137 --> 01:03:00.057
We lift these people up right now to you, Father. We thank you for your divine intervention on their behalf, angelic aid and assistance.

01:03:00.058 --> 01:03:08.556
We bring down these strongholds of self-doubt. We bring down these principalities and powers and rulers over darkness.

01:03:08.557 --> 01:03:22.932
We thank you, Father, that their eyes will see, that they will be enlightened to see and know that you love them, that they are good enough, and that they can come to you boldly before the throne of grace.

01:03:22.933 --> 01:03:52.034
We thank you, Father, that this spirit of feeling that they are not good enough—the unworthiness, the focusing on self—that they would turn their eyes on you and say, "Yes, Lord, I am inadequate; that's why I need you."I need you and I rely on you.

01:03:52.035 --> 01:04:09.556
And the more that they turn their eyes from themselves and turn their eyes toward you, the more they will see and know and walk in the light as you have called them to walk in the light. They will come out of the darkness and into the light.

01:04:09.557 --> 01:04:27.423
We speak that over these people right now, that the eyes of their understanding are enlightened, that they will behold your love for them, that they would have a knowing, and that you would shine your light in their hearts.

01:04:27.424 --> 01:04:38.578
We speak Holy Spirit penetration through that darkness and through that inadequacy, in Jesus'name.

01:04:38.579 --> 01:04:42.452
I believe it is completely free from that because it is a spirit.

01:04:42.453 --> 01:04:50.469
The Lord showed me right then: it is a spirit always telling people they don't have what it takes to get the job done.

01:04:50.470 --> 01:05:00.564
It is the continual bombardment of, 'Why even try?'Like tonight, it is feeling dry—the bombardment of, 'If they experience that, well, I'm inadequate. God doesn't like me, he doesn't care about me.

01:05:00.565 --> 01:05:21.759
Well, where is the Lord in my prayer life?'God loves you, and feeding on the love of God—feeding on what he said—'God so loved the world that he gave his one and only begotten son, that whosoever believes in him should not perish.'I'm the whosoever.

01:05:21.760 --> 01:05:28.295
I am a whosoever. I believe that God loves me and I am adequate.

01:05:28.296 --> 01:05:35.484
God died for me. Jesus paid the price for me. That's it. I hit the vein. That's it.

01:05:35.485 --> 01:05:41.396
He is saying because there are many who don't feel adequate: 'Well, I don't have a good prayer life.

01:05:41.398 --> 01:05:45.220
He doesn't show me angels. He doesn't show me these things, so I'm not adequate tonight.

01:05:45.221 --> 01:05:53.977
I don't feel adequate in my life. Where is the anointing? Where is the Holy Ghost?'You stir yourself up.

01:05:53.978 --> 01:06:06.266
You contend. Are you a contender for the glory? My father loves me. I'm adequate. Why? Because he gave his life for me.

01:06:06.267 --> 01:06:11.919
If he could, if he would have died only just for me, he would have done it.

01:06:11.920 --> 01:06:17.189
If I was the only one for him to die for, I believe he would have died for me.

01:06:17.190 --> 01:06:26.619
I'm that special to him. I'm that special to Jesus. You're that special to Jesus.

01:06:26.620 --> 01:06:30.568
If we were the only ones on this earth, Jesus would have died for me.

01:06:30.569 --> 01:06:44.479
One drop of blood set me free. Jesus paid the price for me. I take authority over the spirit of inadequacy.

01:06:44.480 --> 01:06:49.102
That's so interesting that they're hitting that wall like that and feeling that.

01:06:49.103 --> 01:06:53.273
I know what the Lord is saying right now. So many people have it in their mind.

01:06:53.274 --> 01:07:05.358
They listen to the devil all day long. It's the bombardment of thoughts of inadequacy filling in the dry places.

01:07:05.359 --> 01:07:15.660
'I'm dry. I'm thirsty. He's not here. He must not care.'Where are you?

01:07:15.661 --> 01:07:28.318
Where is this stirring inside of me? I'm so dry. And that's what the Holy Spirit is talking about tonight.

01:07:28.319 --> 01:07:40.703
Where is the father in the dryness? He said, 'I'll never leave you and I'll never forsake you.'Find scriptures just like I'm teaching you.

01:07:40.704 --> 01:07:56.669
Find sermons and stir yourself up. You've got to bite onto the bone and say, 'I'm a bulldog and I'm not letting go until he blesses me.'It's like the wrestling with the angel.

01:07:56.670 --> 01:08:05.151
'I'm not letting go, Jacob. I'm not letting go until you bless me.'And then the angel finally...

01:08:05.152 --> 01:08:29.758
he walked with a little limp. He got what he wanted though. How bad do you want a fresh touch to stir in your life?

01:08:29.759 --> 01:08:41.358
How many of you are dealing with this? I'm just curious. How many of you deal with this feeling of being inadequate?

01:08:41.359 --> 01:08:50.904
How many of you feel that your prayer time is dry? Type one in the comment section. Do you go through dry seasons in your prayer time?

01:08:50.905 --> 01:08:57.633
Is that what the Lord—because I'm coming across this and this is where the river is at.

01:08:57.635 --> 01:09:06.423
How many of you are coming into your prayer time in the mornings and you just feel dry sometimes like this, or you feel that you're inadequate?

01:09:06.424 --> 01:09:17.275
'Well, I'm not good enough. God doesn't love me.'Is there anybody out there who feels that he's abandoned you?

01:09:17.276 --> 01:09:38.635
Maybe you don't feel that. There are days of just, 'I don't even know why I'm even here praying.'I feel it in my spirit. You feel so inadequate.

01:09:38.636 --> 01:09:49.519
Maybe it's not, but I just feel inside of my spirit that God is trying to tell you tonight that he loves you and you are adequate.

01:09:49.520 --> 01:09:56.682
I don't know what it comes to tonight, but it's something so much deeper than just Brandon sitting here pushing through.

01:09:56.683 --> 01:10:04.770
It's trying to tell you that even Brandon has to push through. And you've got to be a bulldog about this.

01:10:04.771 --> 01:10:22.839
And you cannot get down on yourself and think, 'I don't have what it takes.'He wants so bad for you to seek him and you'll find him there in the dryness.

01:10:22.840 --> 01:10:34.879
You are there in the stillness. I refuse to feel inadequate anymore.

01:10:34.880 --> 01:10:43.678
Church leadership, don't look at me. The upper people don't look at you, but Jesus looks at you.

01:10:43.679 --> 01:10:57.279
Regardless of who looked at you, my father died for me. And if I was the only one left on this earth, Christ would have died for me.

01:10:57.280 --> 01:11:06.718
He died for every single one of us. But he died for us to live a life full of abundance.

01:11:06.719 --> 01:11:15.995
But even in the valley of dryness, even in the valley of feeling inadequate, he made me.

01:11:15.996 --> 01:11:23.839
Christ in me. Christ in me, the hope of glory. Christ in me tonight.

01:11:23.840 --> 01:11:33.835
As he is, so am I in this world. I'm moved by that more than I am by the way I feel.

01:11:33.836 --> 01:11:42.639
Faith is not something that you are going to feel. Faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

01:11:42.640 --> 01:11:53.742
Faith is the substance of things hoped for and evidence of things not seen.

01:11:53.743 --> 01:12:00.716
It's not something you've seen. You believe it even when you don't see it.

01:12:00.717 --> 01:12:14.736
Abraham staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God, fully persuaded that what he had promised, he was able also to perform.

01:12:14.737 --> 01:12:23.175
He was fully persuaded in his dryness. It doesn't make sense, and in the deadness of Sarah's womb, he was fully persuaded.

01:12:23.176 --> 01:12:32.393
Even when Sarah couldn't conceive and her ovaries were like raisins—she's like, 'I don't have it. I don't got what it takes.

01:12:32.394 --> 01:12:47.370
I'm inadequate.'But God said, 'Sarah, you're going to have a baby.'And in her inadequacy, he spoke to the dryness in her womb and he said, 'Life be.'And he was not moved by what he saw.

01:12:47.371 --> 01:12:52.465
He was not moved by it. He staggered not at the promise of God.

01:12:52.466 --> 01:12:58.973
'Abraham, you're going to be a father of many nations. Abraham, you're going to walk in the blessing.

01:12:58.974 --> 01:13:59.151
Abraham, you're going to be a father one day.'And he's like, 'I'm old. I don't have...'He trusts God. It's the truth.

01:13:59.153 --> 01:14:23.630
He staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God.

01:14:23.631 --> 01:14:31.148
You can't be moved by what you see, even in the deadness of Sarah's womb, even the deadness of your spiritual walk.

01:14:31.149 --> 01:14:37.818
Somebody said, 'It's the truth, Ruth.'I like that. I'm going to start using that.

01:14:37.819 --> 01:14:42.238
He wasn't moved by what he sees. He was staggered not at the promise of God.

01:14:42.239 --> 01:14:53.524
He knew he was inadequate at that time in his own ability to receive, but God spoke to him and said, 'Either you're going to walk this way or you're not.

01:14:53.525 --> 01:15:01.357
Either you're a believing believer, Abraham, or you're not.'And Abraham grabbed a hold of the promise and said, 'I'm not moved by what I see.

01:15:01.358 --> 01:15:08.352
I'm not moved by what I feel. I'm old. She's old.'That's the same way you do with your spiritual walk.

01:15:08.353 --> 01:15:14.700
I don't feel adequate. God called me; He chose me for such a time as this.

01:15:14.701 --> 01:15:20.474
He let me be born in this time frame, and I know that He didn't make a mistake.

01:15:20.475 --> 01:15:24.878
God doesn't make mistakes. They say, "Well, my mama didn't want me. She was going to have an abortion.

01:15:24.879 --> 01:15:30.799
She didn't even want me; I was an unwanted child."God doesn't make mistakes.

01:15:30.800 --> 01:15:40.613
You're not a mistake. You're here. Your mama had you, and you're a blessing to this earth. God has called you and chose you for such a time as this.

01:15:40.614 --> 01:15:48.193
Regardless of whether she said, "Well, I heard she didn't want me."Well, my dad didn't want another daughter; he wanted a son.

01:15:48.194 --> 01:15:59.467
And I feel inadequate, and I should have been here. You know, my father didn't want me; he wanted a boy instead of a girl, or he wanted a girl instead of a boy.

01:15:59.468 --> 01:16:04.959
But God chose you, and you are who you are. And you're fearfully and wonderfully made.

01:16:04.960 --> 01:16:15.180
There are no mistakes. There are no mistakes. And I'm telling you all, it's time we get a hold of the promises of God.

01:16:15.181 --> 01:16:28.659
He says, "I have a plan for you, I love you, and I died for you individually."And Abraham staggered not at the promise of God, and we need to stagger not at the promise of God.

01:16:28.660 --> 01:16:36.528
What did He promise you in your heart? The desires of your heart. What's in your heart and your biggest desires?

01:16:36.529 --> 01:16:52.422
"I want a relationship with my father."If you're feeling inadequate, a good thing would be to look at the scriptures He said about you and claim them because your job is just to receive it.

01:16:52.423 --> 01:16:56.479
Receive everything He said for you and say it over yourself.

01:16:56.480 --> 01:17:05.836
You said that You knit me together in my mother's womb. You said that I am called this.

01:17:05.837 --> 01:17:13.961
You call me blessed. You call me a blessing. Deuteronomy 28, what I read earlier—You call me these things.

01:17:13.962 --> 01:17:17.673
And I am adequate because You've called me to be adequate even in this.

01:17:17.675 --> 01:17:22.331
And I don't know why I got off on the topic of adequacy, but that's the word the Lord gave me a second ago.

01:17:22.332 --> 01:17:33.168
And He said a lot of them feel that they're going through dry seasons in their prayer life, their marriage, or their job.

01:17:33.169 --> 01:17:36.668
They're going through dry seasons in a lot of areas of their life right now.

01:17:36.669 --> 01:17:44.273
And in 2025, there's a lot of you who are weary in well-doing, ready to let go of the rope.

01:17:44.274 --> 01:17:53.105
"I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me."Call your life a success.

01:17:53.106 --> 01:18:03.942
I heard this right then: get an inner image of it. See yourself as God sees you.

01:18:03.943 --> 01:18:19.759
You have to have that picture. I get the vision inside of me of what He said I could be. See it. See yourself successful.

01:18:19.760 --> 01:18:27.975
You know, maybe if you're a heavy-set guy like me, you look at some buff dude who has huge muscles and say, "That's a vision. I can see myself being that.

01:18:27.976 --> 01:18:43.678
I'm not going to be the heavy guy that's always the fat kid on the playground that nobody wants to pick, the last pick in sports."You have that image of saying, "That's who I am spiritually.

01:18:43.679 --> 01:18:47.127
I'm going to be the muscle man spiritually. I'm going to be the muscle man physically.

01:18:47.128 --> 01:18:55.439
I'm going to take care of my temple."But if you don't see it, you're not going to have an inner image of it to achieve it.

01:18:55.440 --> 01:19:01.180
That's why I drive around rich neighborhoods. People with multi-million dollar houses—they might have a $10 million house.

01:19:01.181 --> 01:19:06.646
I look at them and just park outside. They probably think, "That guy's stalking me."But no, I'm trying to get an image of it.

01:19:06.647 --> 01:19:14.245
If they are of the world and I'm God's kid, how much more could I have that than them?

01:19:14.246 --> 01:19:23.413
They are heathens; they don't know Him, yet they have my harvest and my blessing. And the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the righteous.

01:19:23.414 --> 01:19:27.883
So I drive around getting that image inside of me instead of always thinking poor.

01:19:27.884 --> 01:19:38.238
If you're always around poverty, you can't see blessing. If you're always thinking poor, it's going to stay in you.

01:19:38.239 --> 01:19:46.765
You've got to change the image in your mind from scripture to seeing blessing, thinking blessing. Change your thinking.

01:19:46.766 --> 01:19:55.919
If you're always thinking obese—the Lord always told me, "Brandon, as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he."That's scripture.

01:19:55.920 --> 01:20:03.759
If I see myself as spiritually inadequate—as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

01:20:03.760 --> 01:20:10.820
Same with poverty, same with eating or whatever. If I always see myself as obese, I'll always have it.

01:20:10.821 --> 01:20:16.879
As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he. Out of the abundance of the heart, your mouth speaks.

01:20:16.880 --> 01:20:24.701
I am fit. I am healthy. I will live long and finish strong. I will not have these weight issues anymore.

01:20:24.702 --> 01:20:38.033
I deal with obesity and an eating disorder of thinking—eating for comfort instead of eating for fuel. Well, I'm going to change that.

01:20:38.034 --> 01:20:49.110
You know, but if you keep thinking that—for people who don't deal with that, you don't know until you have an eating disorder and you go, "Man, this is something where I'm calling those things that are not as though they were."I don't want to deal with this.

01:20:49.111 --> 01:20:57.256
I break this generational curse off of my life. My mom was fat, her mom was fat, and her dad was fat.

01:20:57.257 --> 01:21:05.445
No, I don't have that. My kids won't deal with that. It stops with me.

01:21:05.446 --> 01:21:10.322
Poverty stops with me. Well, my mom and dad were poor, and their mom and dad were poor.

01:21:10.323 --> 01:21:16.300
Everybody was poor. You know, my great-granny, who is 106 years old, dealt with poverty.

01:21:16.301 --> 01:21:28.399
No, poverty stops with me. You've got to get that inside of you. I am going to walk with the King.

01:21:28.400 --> 01:21:33.890
So, going back to it, I will have a spiritual walk where I feel adequate.

01:21:33.891 --> 01:21:38.420
God's called me. And dryness is only for a season; I'm not going to be dry.

01:21:38.421 --> 01:21:46.166
Tomorrow's another day. You've got to keep going. Does that help you all? I mean, this is just what's coming out of my spirit now.

01:21:46.167 --> 01:21:50.384
And I'm thankful for it because I didn't know where to go, and now all of a sudden, this is falling.

01:21:50.385 --> 01:21:56.078
So I'm like, "Okay, Holy Ghost, thank you for helping me."It's just real, y'all.

01:21:56.079 --> 01:22:04.542
And I'm telling y'all, this is what you do. The Lord said, "Lead by example"earlier, and I was like, "Lead by example?

01:22:04.543 --> 01:22:15.119
Well, I don't know where I'm going. What do you want me to do?"Okay.

01:22:15.120 --> 01:22:24.528
Hallelujah. So, Father, we just keep pouring it out. I sure love you, Braden.

01:22:24.529 --> 01:22:35.919
Braden knows; he gets it because he was raised by us. But Father, we just thank You, Lord.

01:22:35.920 --> 01:22:45.678
We just thank You, Father, for Your hand on us. Now, Father, after I got through that, is there anything You want to show us?

01:22:45.679 --> 01:22:52.370
Lord, I just felt like that was something. So, whenever I got to that, Lord, I really felt like it was a lot.

01:22:52.371 --> 01:23:00.638
It was just what You wanted to say tonight about that. But Lord, I still feel an urgency to pray for things.

01:23:00.639 --> 01:25:23.525
Is there anything coming for the nations tonight that You want me to relay to the people?

01:25:23.526 --> 01:25:31.119
I'm telling you, I'm hitting that wall. He spoke about feeling inadequate.

01:25:31.120 --> 01:25:40.158
It's all about the people feeling that they don't have what it takes to finish the race.

01:25:40.159 --> 01:26:04.238
They are adequate, but there's such a wound in people—a deep sorrow of feeling the inadequacy.

01:26:04.239 --> 01:26:11.759
"I don't have what it takes."I hear them in their thoughts. "I don't have what it takes.

01:26:11.760 --> 01:26:30.879
Where's God for me? Where is God for me?"He says, "Where is God for me?

01:26:30.880 --> 01:26:44.673
I feel so abandoned. I feel so alone."It's very interesting coming up to that wall.

01:26:44.674 --> 01:26:52.313
You feel it. You can feel it. You can hear them. There's so many people saying that inside of their hearts: "Where is God for me?

01:26:52.314 --> 01:27:00.130
I feel so inadequate. My prayer language isn't enough. I don't pray in tongues well enough.

01:27:00.131 --> 01:27:11.575
I don't hear God well enough."I don't pray in tongues well enough.

01:27:11.577 --> 01:27:29.881
I feel so inadequate for where I want to be. How come I don't hear God?

01:27:29.882 --> 01:27:46.518
They say, 'I don't feel like I hear God. How do I know if it is God when he is talking to me?'I feel so alone.

01:27:46.519 --> 01:28:00.959
Don't you see? How do I know when it's God talking to me? I feel so inadequate tonight.

01:28:00.960 --> 01:28:15.678
I feel so alone. Nobody understands me. These are the things I'm hearing.

01:28:15.679 --> 01:28:31.919
Does he really truly care about me? I'm at the end of my rope. Don't you see?

01:28:31.920 --> 01:28:51.279
Why have you abandoned me? God probably cares, but he doesn't care about me.

01:28:51.280 --> 01:28:57.461
See how the enemy would try to build all this around you? There's so much of that I'm hearing.

01:28:57.462 --> 01:29:08.638
And those are lies from the devil. He feeds those lies because it goes strictly against his word.

01:29:08.639 --> 01:29:17.919
But because you are moved by what you see, you are allowing your flesh to dominate you and your thoughts.

01:29:17.920 --> 01:29:28.859
It's why I keep telling you: I'm not moved by what I see. I'm not moved by what I feel. I'm moved by what the Word of God says. My Father loves me.

01:29:28.860 --> 01:29:52.239
First John 4:7-8 says: 'Beloved, let us love one another, for love is of God; and everyone that loveth is born of God and knoweth God.

01:29:52.240 --> 01:30:16.959
He that loveth not knoweth not God, for God is love.'Beloved, let us love one another. That's where it's at.

01:30:16.960 --> 01:30:24.636
But you've got to know inside of you that all those things that you're hearing, and what I'm hearing you saying...

01:30:24.637 --> 01:30:33.039
it's interesting. In the vision that I just had, I saw what looked like a whirlwind.

01:30:33.040 --> 01:30:41.599
It was a big drain. And each person was like a YouTube screen.

01:30:41.600 --> 01:30:51.519
You know how you can scan the thumbnails and see all the different pictures?

01:30:51.520 --> 01:30:57.034
There were literally thousands of your faces going in a whirlwind.

01:30:57.035 --> 01:31:05.249
It was a drain before me, and each one had a person inside, and everybody was saying something all at once.

01:31:05.250 --> 01:31:14.966
And as it's moving in this drain, as I'm praying, I hear you saying this from your heart—the things that I was repeating just then.

01:31:14.967 --> 01:31:20.605
I was hearing it, and as that would swing by, I could hear you getting louder as it hit my ear.

01:31:20.606 --> 01:31:30.739
It moved away, and I could hear you for a split second moving by me, and you were going down the drain.

01:31:30.740 --> 01:31:38.404
Your thoughts are going down the drain. It's trash. Don't think it.

01:31:38.405 --> 01:31:44.796
What you meditate on the most is what you'll become. You've got to change your thought pattern.

01:31:44.797 --> 01:31:51.983
I saw it turning before me, and as I was turning, each one of you was moving before me.

01:31:51.984 --> 01:31:56.241
I could hear your thoughts. I could hear what you were saying inside of your heart.

01:31:56.242 --> 01:32:59.198
All those things that I was repeating just a second ago. There's this lady—somebody who lives in an apartment with steps going up.

01:32:59.199 --> 01:33:04.158
You live in an apartment complex, and you're walking up these steps.

01:33:04.159 --> 01:33:20.213
There is gray siding on your building. You live on the second floor, and you're crying out for more.

01:33:20.214 --> 01:33:35.704
I see where you live as this thing's moving around. You walked up the steps, and you live in the door on the right-hand side.

01:33:35.705 --> 01:33:45.168
I can see your steps. I can see where you are. You live right where the steps end, in that door right there.

01:33:45.169 --> 01:34:19.809
There's a window right here. I see where you're living. There looked like some snow at the bottom of your steps in the yard.

01:34:19.810 --> 01:34:48.479
Oh Lord, you're giving the Lord an ultimatum: 'Either you fix this in me, or I'm going to do something to myself.'That's what you say. 'I'm not going to live like this anymore.

01:34:48.480 --> 01:35:02.477
I'm giving you until this time frame to fix this, or I'm going to do this.'You're crying out to the Father so much that your heart is grieving.

01:35:02.478 --> 01:35:16.399
You're so empty. You're single. You don't have a husband or even a boyfriend.

01:35:16.400 --> 01:35:52.085
You say, 'I'm tired of being alone. No one to even call on the phone.'Oh, I see it.

01:35:52.086 --> 01:36:06.559
Ma'am, you're so hurt, but Jesus loves you so much—so much that he would show me this right now. He has a plan for your life.

01:36:06.560 --> 01:36:34.627
'Come unto me, all ye that are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.'As you're climbing those steps at night by yourself and you go into that empty room and live in that cold apartment, watching TV by yourself...

01:36:34.628 --> 01:36:53.359
you watch us on this YouTube, and Jesus sees you right where you are.

01:36:53.360 --> 01:37:26.276
I don't know what that white is—if it's not snow, it's dead grass for sure. He wants to become so real to you.

01:37:26.278 --> 01:37:38.220
There's so many of you—this probably fits a category, not maybe of the apartment complex, but you're saying the exact same thing she's saying: 'I'm so alone.

01:37:38.221 --> 01:37:44.394
I have nobody.'During this holiday season, it's even harder on you.

01:37:44.395 --> 01:37:54.311
You think, 'Does God care?'But I'm telling you, God cares. He cares about you being alone.

01:37:54.312 --> 01:38:06.959
He cares about you feeling like you have nobody to call on the phone. Jesus cares about you.

01:38:06.960 --> 01:38:16.959
Instead of saying, 'If this doesn't change, I'm ending it all,'say, 'This is the beginning of my new start.

01:38:16.960 --> 01:38:38.799
As of tonight, this is the beginning of my new start.'I have something to live for.

01:38:38.800 --> 01:39:50.799
God has so much more in store. That's beautiful. The sorrow is no longer.

01:39:50.800 --> 01:39:56.711
Thank you, Lord, for all that you have in store—that in 2026 we will soar.

01:39:56.712 --> 01:40:07.226
Father, I thank you. The greater the days ahead. The more you have for us.

01:40:07.227 --> 01:40:47.662
Oh, Father, I thank you, Lord. Stir inside yourself. We call it a move in your spirit man.

01:40:47.663 --> 01:42:42.650
We call it stirred in the name of Jesus. Oh, Father, we thank you, Lord, for fresh fire of the Holy Ghost.

01:42:42.651 --> 01:42:48.631
We thank you for the Holy Spirit, Lord, that you move inside of these individuals tonight.

01:42:48.632 --> 01:43:31.809
You stir inside of them. Do you have anything, hun? I find that it's harder when my Word level's low. It's harder when I get busy.

01:43:31.810 --> 01:43:48.958
That feeling of inadequacy has a lot to do with how I was raised, because I was abused as a child and it tried to make me feel inadequate.

01:43:48.959 --> 01:44:01.413
But the Lord has brought me so far from where I was. I feel like as I get in the word more, it's helped me a lot.

01:44:01.414 --> 01:44:08.635
It's just staying—it's not allowing the thoughts. It's just fighting the good fight of faith.

01:44:08.636 --> 01:44:20.168
On days whenever it's like that, I put Kathryn Kuhlman on or I listen to it, and it helps.

01:44:20.169 --> 01:44:25.431
It's like you're getting punched, and when you're getting punched, you don't succumb to it.

01:44:25.432 --> 01:44:34.937
You have to fight. You get even with what you're just saying right then about being abused. People don't know your story.

01:44:34.938 --> 01:44:42.614
A lot of people don't know your childhood and being raised—you were sometimes in a car for how many months without food?

01:44:42.615 --> 01:44:46.879
Yeah. Well, okay, so you want me to tell the story? You can say some of it.

01:44:46.880 --> 01:44:50.466
A lot of people need to hear it. You don't ever talk. So, that's what I'm saying.

01:44:50.467 --> 01:44:55.439
There's a lot of people who don't know your story about you and how you were raised.

01:44:55.440 --> 01:45:02.312
Your dad was a preacher. Yes. I was raised Baptist. No, not Baptist.

01:45:02.313 --> 01:45:12.126
Sorry, he was not Baptist. I'm Assemblies of God. He was an Assemblies of God pastor; that's a lot different.

01:45:12.127 --> 01:45:21.256
Yeah, we were too Pentecostal for that. It's late, but that is what he—I'm not laughing at you.

01:45:21.257 --> 01:45:27.650
I just, when you say Baptist, I was like... I messed it up. You're AG, Assemblies of God.

01:45:27.651 --> 01:45:38.088
Yes, Assemblies of God pastor. Well, they got a divorce when I was 11, but he had been abused a lot as a kid, too.

01:45:38.089 --> 01:45:46.869
So, he brought that. It just came in because they wanted a boy and they had me.

01:45:46.870 --> 01:45:51.734
My mom told me that she wished that I was a boy because that was what they wanted.

01:45:51.735 --> 01:46:03.888
So, I knew that from a small child. And then he was abusive. My dad was abusive to me. Whenever I was in church, I got pinched if I moved.

01:46:03.889 --> 01:46:10.120
If I said the wrong thing, I got spankings all the time, more than any of my other siblings.

01:46:10.121 --> 01:46:23.220
And just a lot of hard stuff like I don't really like talking about, but we lived in a car for a long time because my dad would just disappear.

01:46:23.221 --> 01:46:38.843
He got let go from his pastoral job at the Assemblies of God, and it really derailed him a lot, so it kind of affected how he acted even more.

01:46:38.844 --> 01:46:45.239
He didn't take any other job. So, he was at home a lot with me and my mom was gone a lot.

01:46:45.240 --> 01:46:56.674
I was abused probably the most out of my siblings, physically and verbally, but never sexually.

01:46:56.675 --> 01:47:01.613
Thank the Lord for that. I think He was definitely praying for me.

01:47:01.614 --> 01:47:09.723
So, definitely keep praying for your spouse—the one that you're going to meet, that God has for you.

01:47:09.724 --> 01:47:16.815
Pray for them because you don't realize that they might really need that, because I feel like that really helped me.

01:47:16.816 --> 01:47:23.456
The Lord kept me through all of that. We would have so many good miracles in the middle of that.

01:47:23.457 --> 01:47:33.318
As kids, we were homeschooled a lot, but my dad took us away from friends and family, so we weren't around anybody.

01:47:33.319 --> 01:47:45.430
When we went to places, I would get in trouble for saying the wrong thing or doing the wrong thing because I was a pastor's kid, so I would get in trouble behind the scenes more than anything.

01:47:45.431 --> 01:47:53.288
It affected the way I acted, the way I talked, it affected everything.

01:47:53.289 --> 01:48:05.989
When you're a child and you're in that delicate growing stage and you are dealing with so much of that, I didn't realize how much it affected me.

01:48:05.990 --> 01:48:11.537
But that was just a crucible. I think that's what a lot of you probably have dealt with. I mean, I know I'm not the only one.

01:48:11.538 --> 01:48:20.877
There's a lot of people who have dealt with childhood abuse, whether it's verbally, physically, or sexually.

01:48:20.878 --> 01:48:27.075
I know I'm not alone. I know there's people that have had it way worse than me.

01:48:27.076 --> 01:48:36.041
We lived in a car. We ate ketchup packets for a while, and a lot of different things.

01:48:36.042 --> 01:48:45.622
My dad would disappear. We bathed in the truck stop with a sink. We went to the truck stop and we would take baths in the sink.

01:48:45.623 --> 01:48:54.849
Sometimes we would go to a church and my dad would just travel there, and he would get in with the people and the pastors, and they would like him.

01:48:54.850 --> 01:49:01.514
Then he would get the keys or something—he wouldn't tell them—but we lived in the church. We lived in the back of the church.

01:49:01.515 --> 01:49:09.060
I remember they would all leave and he was pretending to lock up, and then we hid our stuff under a table at the church in the back.

01:49:09.061 --> 01:49:13.252
We would pull the stuff out, like blankets and stuff, and we slept there.

01:49:13.253 --> 01:49:18.074
For years it was like that, and then he would just disappear.

01:49:18.075 --> 01:49:26.559
I remember so many birthdays where he wasn't there, and my mom was trying to work a lot, so she was really just absent a lot.

01:49:26.560 --> 01:49:43.433
I kind of had times when I had to fend for myself and just a lot of traumatizing little things like that through my whole entire childhood.

01:49:43.434 --> 01:49:50.940
It really affected me in ways that I still feel like the Lord's bringing me out of.

01:49:50.941 --> 01:49:56.272
All that to say, I don't like to focus on all that, but just because y'all haven't heard that story—that's just the CliffsNotes.

01:49:56.273 --> 01:50:06.816
That's the CliffsNotes, but a lot of the stuff that she deals with is from rejection.

01:50:06.818 --> 01:50:14.679
Rejection is—and you're still getting through it. Yes. It's in layers. It feels like an onion.

01:50:14.680 --> 01:50:22.013
I will go, 'I forgive him, I forgive him.'None of my siblings talk to my dad, but I will talk to him.

01:50:22.014 --> 01:50:27.708
I talked to him on the phone, but then he'll just change his phone number and I can't get a hold of him still.

01:50:27.709 --> 01:50:35.388
But I forgave him, and that took so much work with the Lord, with the Holy Spirit, for me to even be able to get there.

01:50:35.389 --> 01:50:47.111
But it's layers. It's not something that happens overnight.

01:50:47.112 --> 01:50:52.060
You have to be in partnership with the Holy Spirit on a day-to-day basis.

01:50:52.061 --> 01:51:22.365
I rely so much on him and he'll say—just taking a lot of time to listen and not talk so much because I know a lot of times in the past, whenever you feel like you're just pouring your guts out to God and you're just talking and talking and talking, it feels like—I relied so much as a kid on making good grades because that's how I got my parents'attention, so it taught me to be more sense-ruled.

01:51:22.366 --> 01:51:37.160
Thinking using intelligence instead of—because I saw in the spirit as a kid and my dad one time freaked out on me because I said I was talking to an angel, and he was like, 'Well, what was it saying?

01:51:37.161 --> 01:51:41.311
Don't ever do that again.'So it made me question a lot of things.

01:51:41.312 --> 01:51:51.225
All of those things combined, and having a bad relationship with my dad, has really affected how I have had to work at having a relationship with God.

01:51:51.226 --> 01:52:01.233
I know there's a lot of people out here that have had bad relationships with parents, or an absent dad, orphans and all of that.

01:52:01.234 --> 01:52:12.816
When you don't have a good father, or one that's there or one that you're able to talk to, it does affect your relationship with God.

01:52:12.817 --> 01:52:31.953
It affects how you can come to him because when your earthly father is gone or he's never there, or he says, 'I'll come to your birthday,'but then he never comes, you have that expectation, especially when you're a child, that it affects you and how you view your relationship with God.

01:52:31.954 --> 01:52:41.619
And then after Megan got diagnosed and all of that, it really just takes away that trust.

01:52:41.620 --> 01:52:46.827
It tries to affect that trust that you've trusted him. Lord, I trust you.

01:52:46.828 --> 01:52:52.957
And so I had to just come to the point where I was like, 'God, I don't feel like I can completely trust you.

01:52:52.958 --> 01:53:04.382
I want to; I need you to help me to get there.'And so doing that and just pouring my guts out to him every day, he'll say, 'Diana, do this'in these little things.

01:53:04.383 --> 01:53:11.858
But a lot of times when you're sin-ruled, you think, 'I have to...

01:53:11.859 --> 01:53:19.036
if it doesn't happen this way...'You feel like, 'I have to do this to make God accept me'because that's the way my parents were.

01:53:19.037 --> 01:53:22.726
With my earthly parents, I had to make good grades for them to accept me.

01:53:22.727 --> 01:53:32.790
So you feel like you have to do this much prayer, this much time, this much work to get there. And then if I do this, then he looks at me.

01:53:32.791 --> 01:53:55.487
If I fast for five hours a day, or if I fast for a month—however long it is—if I read an X amount of time to the point where it becomes where I think a lot of believers get to that point where you feel like you have to earn God's favor, right?

01:53:55.488 --> 01:54:03.131
You have to earn God's anointing. You have to earn God's hand on your life. But it's by grace.

01:54:03.132 --> 01:54:10.232
And that's why I try to tell her all the time: you don't have to do anything for God to love you. He already loves you. He already died for you.

01:54:10.233 --> 01:54:20.358
And that's why I tell her all the time, no matter how much you went through high school and college with a 4.0 and graduated summa cum laude, and you were brilliant.

01:54:20.359 --> 01:54:30.808
It was always her way of having people approve of her, of being the best that she was because she was the top of her class.

01:54:30.809 --> 01:54:37.700
But I've told her there's nothing you can do to get God to love you more than he already does.

01:54:37.701 --> 01:54:45.264
And that's what I felt like I had to do in order to gain their attention. I felt like I had to do that.

01:54:45.265 --> 01:54:54.786
So it taught me to be more sin-ruled than faith-ruled, to do more works.

01:54:54.787 --> 01:55:19.470
And that's what comes with the relationship of the Lord, thinking that a lot of believers think, 'Well, if I fast five days a week or read 20 chapters a week in my Bible, maybe I'll have a little bit more anointing on my life to do something.'But it's all by grace.

01:55:19.471 --> 01:55:28.211
There's nothing you can do to get God to love you anymore. He already loves you unconditionally. It's how we yield to him.

01:55:28.212 --> 01:55:35.733
'Father, I give more to you.'That's what I tell her all the time, feeling inadequate from that abuse as a father, thinking...

01:55:35.734 --> 01:55:52.158
and then when Megan got diagnosed, it derailed Diana. I'm going to tell you all, at that time—what was it, 20 years ago?—I didn't think she was going to come out of it.

01:55:52.159 --> 01:55:59.729
At that time, when I was in the marriage, it was the darkest I've ever seen her of any human.

01:55:59.730 --> 01:56:06.077
It was awful. After her dad and all that, I thought, 'Man, our life is starting out. We got married.

01:56:06.078 --> 01:56:19.515
Everything's great.'And when Megan got diagnosed with autism and they told her that she would never come out of a five-year-old level, that for the rest of her life she'll probably be at an 18-month level mentally.

01:56:19.516 --> 01:56:26.876
And that was the darkest hour for me. I just thought there's no way our marriage is going to make this.

01:56:26.877 --> 01:56:45.836
That's what I thought in the natural because of how much depression she overcame and then pulling ourselves out of this and getting over it and being able to say, 'God, I trust you even through this storm.'And that whole thing started another spiral of blaming.

01:56:45.837 --> 01:56:53.552
Because when I was a kid, it was, 'Who did this? You're wrong.'You get a spanking, and whoever did this wrong is...

01:56:53.553 --> 01:56:59.946
and because of the abuse and stuff, I had a big problem with who's to blame.

01:56:59.947 --> 01:57:03.316
Whose fault is it? So I blamed myself because I'm the mother.

01:57:03.318 --> 01:57:07.705
The buck stops here. It's my fault. But I couldn't find out what I did wrong.

01:57:07.706 --> 01:57:12.286
I did everything I was supposed to do. 'It's my fault Megan's this way.

01:57:12.287 --> 01:57:19.495
I did everything I was supposed to do. I never drank. I never did any drugs. I didn't do anything wrong the whole time.

01:57:19.496 --> 01:57:26.111
No sin at all.'So I thought, 'Well, maybe I should have cleaned up my diet better.

01:57:26.112 --> 01:57:41.598
Maybe I ate something.'It was little things, stupid things, but those are the things that kind of tried to wedge in there that the enemy tries to bring to derail you. And so that's just what I went through.

01:57:41.599 --> 01:57:55.716
And I think that's why I try, even with the inadequacy of doing this channel—it tries to wear on you and me still to feel like, 'What has God called us to do?'Do we feel that we can talk in front of millions of people?

01:57:55.717 --> 01:58:00.781
It tries to bring that self-doubt of what God's called you to do.

01:58:00.782 --> 01:58:04.660
And that's why I try to be real with y'all. It's a lot of pressure.

01:58:04.661 --> 01:58:08.530
And that's why I say I'm not here to perform. I'm just being me.

01:58:08.531 --> 01:58:14.012
And if I wasn't praying in front of you all, I'm going to be praying all the time anyway. That's what we do.

01:58:14.013 --> 01:58:28.022
So I just try to make it public and I try to really cut out all the spiritual celebrity performance, the major TV networks, the people that have huge ministries.

01:58:28.023 --> 01:58:34.814
I don't try to be the stereotype of this. I just go, 'I'm just normal. I'm Brandon and Diana. We're here. We got issues.

01:58:34.815 --> 01:58:45.653
We're all working through this, but we're here to pray.'And I see things, and the Lord shows me things, and I just try to make it as real as I can with y'all.

01:58:45.654 --> 01:58:51.315
Well, it's just that inadequacy, that feeling of when you're feeling like you're not good enough.

01:58:51.316 --> 01:58:59.514
And whenever it gets to where you hit the bottom and you say, 'I can't do this.'And then he says, 'Thank you.

01:58:59.515 --> 01:59:03.284
You finally admitted you can't do this.'That's exactly what he said.

01:59:03.285 --> 01:59:07.116
And that's what happened. I said, 'I can't do this. I can't be enough.

01:59:07.117 --> 01:59:12.886
I'm not enough.'And he said, 'You're right. You're not enough, Diana. You need me.

01:59:12.887 --> 01:59:23.985
It's not because you're good; it's because I'm good.'And so getting to that place and realizing that I'm not the victim. It's not about me.

01:59:23.986 --> 01:59:40.675
Stopping focusing on me and focusing on what God can do through me, and allowing that hurt to go away and just saying, 'No, I refuse to be the victim. I am not... what I have been through doesn't define me.

01:59:40.676 --> 01:59:55.872
It's what God can use and what I can yield to him, and he can flow through me.'Allowing me to be the best at what he's called me to be in this season and him pulling back those layers of me homeschooling my kids and saying, 'This is...

01:59:55.873 --> 02:00:03.198
you're doing this,'and seeing my kids flourish and grow, and seeing the joy.

02:00:03.199 --> 02:00:13.757
And just saying, 'You know what? It's not about this. It's just part of the chapter. It's just part of the book.

02:00:13.758 --> 02:00:34.057
It's not defining us.'It's focusing more on others because when you're focused so much on yourself, it tries to wedge a layer of pride and you don't even realize it because that woe-is-me mentality is also a form.

02:00:34.058 --> 02:00:42.953
It's a sneaky way that the enemy tries to get in and build pride.

02:00:42.954 --> 02:00:45.379
Sorry, I can't see your eyes very well. I don't have makeup on.

02:00:45.380 --> 02:00:55.833
It's late at night. I don't care about no makeup. Come on, cowgirl.

02:00:55.834 --> 02:01:01.197
I can't see them beautiful eyes. I'm trying to see you. I don't care if you don't have no makeup on.

02:01:01.198 --> 02:01:05.084
And they don't. I don't care. Whatever they think, whatever.

02:01:05.085 --> 02:01:12.156
But I feel like people need to hear more about your story. I feel like people need to know more about you.

02:01:12.157 --> 02:01:18.234
I know I talk a lot, but they never know. You're always the quiet one in the corner, but there's so much depth to you.

02:01:18.235 --> 02:01:29.045
And I feel like you're a gift to the people. People need to know that you've been through hell and you've not been burned.

02:01:29.046 --> 02:01:35.198
You have some go on. You struggle a little something, but you're still marching with me and we're still going in.

02:01:35.199 --> 02:01:41.495
The Lord kept me; it's the only reason I'm still here, truly.

02:01:41.496 --> 02:01:47.994
Because we pray and I believe it's the relationship that you've developed.

02:01:47.995 --> 02:01:55.197
They need to hear that even at the most of what we go through, we still have our stuff we're walking through.

02:01:55.198 --> 02:01:58.992
You still have your stuff you're walking through. Tell them we felt the inadequacy.

02:01:58.993 --> 02:02:04.815
I thought it was interesting because it went along with some of the conversations we've had. It doesn't go away; it's like you have to resist it.

02:02:04.816 --> 02:02:11.916
'Resist the devil and he will flee.'If he knows your weakness and knows your history, he knows your past and he'll try to sneak in.

02:02:11.917 --> 02:02:19.992
You'll feel great and everything's great, the Lord's working through this and you feel like you've made so much progress, and then he just comes right in that one day and tries to knock you down.

02:02:19.993 --> 02:02:31.664
You say, 'No, having done all to stand, stand therefore.'You get back up and you fight the good fight of faith, and it's just keeping on going and not letting that derail you because we are soldiers for Christ.

02:02:31.665 --> 02:02:38.408
We're marching on. We're doing this for the kingdom. We have a job to do.

02:02:38.409 --> 02:02:50.216
No matter how seemingly insignificant you may feel that it is, even if it's just raising your children, you're being very effective.

02:02:50.217 --> 02:02:59.710
That is one of the most important jobs you can do, and being a good spouse. As women and wives, we are called to be the helpmate.

02:02:59.711 --> 02:03:11.919
He made us to be a helpmate to support our husbands, to uplift them, pray for them, extol them, and support them in everything.

02:03:11.920 --> 02:03:20.158
I think a lot of times, even with women, it's gotten out of control with the whole girl power 'hear me roar'thing.

02:03:20.159 --> 02:03:40.505
